Implemented the double-agent TDD flow as a real `duh tdd` feature, with the ADR written first in [ADR-076](</Users/nomind/Code/Tengu/tengu-cockpit/benchmarks/double-agent-tdd/worktrees/codex-gpt54/docs/adrs/ADR-076-double-agent-tdd.md>). The orchestration lives in [duh/tdd.py](</Users/nomind/Code/Tengu/tengu-cockpit/benchmarks/double-agent-tdd/worktrees/codex-gpt54/duh/tdd.py>) and reuses D.U.H.’s existing child-agent/session infrastructure; the CLI entry point is [duh/cli/tdd.py](</Users/nomind/Code/Tengu/tengu-cockpit/benchmarks/double-agent-tdd/worktrees/codex-gpt54/duh/cli/tdd.py>) with parser/main wiring in the existing CLI modules.

Docs were updated in [README.md](</Users/nomind/Code/Tengu/tengu-cockpit/benchmarks/double-agent-tdd/worktrees/codex-gpt54/README.md>), plus a new wiki page [docs/wiki/Double-Agent-TDD.md](</Users/nomind/Code/Tengu/tengu-cockpit/benchmarks/double-agent-tdd/worktrees/codex-gpt54/docs/wiki/Double-Agent-TDD.md>) and sidebar linkage. Tests were added for phase ordering, RED vs GREEN distinction, refactor application before validation, CLI parsing/dispatch, and a stub-provider-backed end-to-end flow in [tests/unit/test_double_agent_tdd.py](</Users/nomind/Code/Tengu/tengu-cockpit/benchmarks/double-agent-tdd/worktrees/codex-gpt54/tests/unit/test_double_agent_tdd.py>) and [tests/integration/test_double_agent_tdd_flow.py](</Users/nomind/Code/Tengu/tengu-cockpit/benchmarks/double-agent-tdd/worktrees/codex-gpt54/tests/integration/test_double_agent_tdd_flow.py>).

